review:
This game is 100% dead. You can never fight in "Duels", you can never fight in "Tournaments" and you can never sink the Lucky Wheel because every moment you try the game would tell you that there are "CONNECTION PROBLEMS".
https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2650570188
https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2650570109
https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2650570018
The developers have obviously abandoned this game years ago so I advice you to avoid playing this game. Not only that but the battles in "City" mode are terribly imbalanced with the enemies continuously healing themselves with infinite potions but you, as the player, have to constantly spend money to buy potions.

This game seemingly has potential... but the developers left it as a pile of pig manure.

author: {'steamid': '76561198840434765', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 9, 'playtime_forever': 31, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 31, 'last_played': 1557206724}
review:
I tried playing this charming little title and actually liked everything for about 10-15 mins :p, no but really this game is dead, the message board is dead, online matchmaking is just a loading screen of sadness now and to top it all off... it's kinda cool at first and that pisses me off really because I want to 100% hate this game but can't all in all lol :/. Soooo pretty much the graphics aren't bad and even the music isn't horrible, in fact if I was on steam during its release I'd be writing a positive review I'm sure so honestly it's depressing to see RoShamBo in it's current decaying state. The fact that it's still a pay to win at this point is stupid beyond comprehension as well considering thats a dead dog game like this can't possibly be played enough to warrant a payment system anymore and should be taken off until further notice.

I just think this could have been cool if done right in start of things and they weren't and thats that lol, I give this game a 3/10 because of potential at one point and the graphic and sound isn't bad, I am deleting this title once I'm done posting this but message me if anyone plays this game still, I'm truly curious to find out why haha :p.

the items kind of help you to win, either by blocking damage or doing more damage. other than that, there is no active thinking involved or skills. just upgrade attack and defence, and spin the wheel daily, to win teeth or cash. believe it or not, saving these currencies for a good item is a good stratedgy. however, it is still luck based.

the pvp takes a few mins to find someone but is fair.

author: {'steamid': '76561198327883405', 'num_games_owned': 1035, 'num_reviews': 15, 'playtime_forever': 4890, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3762, 'last_played': 1493954106}
review:
I'm ashamed that I spent as much time on this game as I did. All you do is fight duels, tournaments and fight in the city. It gets old after awhile.

I was trying to throw fights in the Duels in order to get the Loser Gold achievement because I was winning a lot more than I was losing but even though the game counts those as losses, Steam counts them as wins for some reason and I ended up getting the Killer Gold achievement without winning 500 duels in the game, don't know if that's Steam's screw-up or that of the developers but anyway, I was trying to win duels so I could earn that achievement rightfully in the game, but shortly thereafter, I kept getting harassed by one of the admins in duels, I could tell it was an admin because I was fighting the same guy over and over again and it wasn't taking me as long to get into fights.

Guess I'm too powerful or they're mad I accidentally exploited one of their glitches, speaking of which, sometimes the game glitched up on me on my computer.

Also, the game would crash occasionally when I would do duels or tournaments and the game would count that as a loss, I tried asking about that and never got a response back. And yes, I paid to get more powerful, such bull crap that I had to resort to that in order to have a fighting chance rather than be able to earn it without using real world currency.

Bad freemium games make Santa very unhappy, enough to, uh, never mind.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jpFeAd-JVgU&feature=youtu.be

5:55

author: {'steamid': '76561198055290451', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 8, 'playtime_forever': 61, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 58, 'last_played': 1469239073}
review:
Shortly, DO NOT PLAY THIS GAME. DO NOT WASTE YOUR TIME NOR YOUR MONEY WITH IT.

Observation: I got the Starter Fighter for free, so my experience was a easier gameplay, compared to a average guy. Consider it while reading.

That was the most cash-based game i ever played. It's not just pay-to-win, it's PAY-TO-PLAY.

To begin, the shop is divided in items you can buy with in-game money and items you can buy with cash. You actually can get cash playing, but, of course, in minimal amounts and as i tried, you can't buy everything up to your level without grinding. The few minutes i played was enough to run out of money, both in-game and cash (remember i got the Starter pack?).

The gameplay could be a little more interesting if it wasn't luck-based only. And I actually think(not sure) from my experience that your chance of error against the CPU increases as you progress the campaign.

As any "good" pay-to-win game, you begin with the worst character possible and have to get higher grade characters and very early they become your enemy in the campaign (i just played a few minutes, but already encountered them).

For real, you can't play this game without spending money, so DO NOT PLAY THIS GAME. There are a lot of better options, even for free.

author: {'steamid': '76561197992153921', 'num_games_owned': 162, 'num_reviews': 44, 'playtime_forever': 30, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 30, 'last_played': 1471086651}
review:
normaly i have to play a few rounds of pvp in mutliplayer games to get a feel for the game.

first match i was paired with somebody of the same level except they were completely decked in p2w gear.
no punches thrown, i just leave the match.
says i recieve no teeth or exp (i hope he recieved nothing as well)  which is fair i dont expect to be rewarded for NOT wasting my time.

second matched with same level opponent,  attempted to tic-tac-toe,  seems my opponent keeps making the exact same choice i make,  but they do "dirty tricks" and kill me ???

well ok,  im not spending anymore time on this game.

i probably wouldnt get so frustrated if it didnt take so long to get a match started and didnt spend so much time inbetween fights.

maybe just providing immediates matches against different opponents (DIFFERENT OPPONENTS EACH MATCH) would have aleviated the majority of frustration felt from two negetive back to back experiences.

also the tutorial took too long and was too wordy.
it was as if it was trying to be funny but never really delivered any wit or humor and was over all too wordy.
too many speach bubbles filled with too many words.
just explain "tic tac toe"   and then explain the rest of the game in simple and cogent and precise manner.
the tutorial is simply meant for instructions about how to play.
by the time i was 1/5th through the tutorial i felt i already knew what to do but i couldnt escape the tediousness of the wall of speach bubbles.   like a fool i read each speach bubble instead of just spamming click to skip - in hopes to find advice or instructions - but it was just a bunch of BLAH BLAH BLAH.
need a TLDR button for the tutorial :p

author: {'steamid': '76561198047975857', 'num_games_owned': 94, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 41, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 41, 'last_played': 1469390688}
review:
Interesting approach to a good old "rock, paper, scissors". 
You can have a character with health points, items & some abilities, like block next attack, do an increased damage on next turn, heal yourself and many others. 
At the start it seems quite fun, but when you go to online, you'll see how donation system works :( 
Your opponents will have twice as much hp as your character, do a double damage compare to you :( So the only thing to win against them, hope for a luck. A very big chunck of luck :D

Overall: p2w, mostly depends on luck. So, personally, I don't see any advantages of putting money into this game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198004983184', 'num_games_owned': 1299, 'num_reviews': 91, 'playtime_forever': 33, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 33, 'last_played': 1469229453}
review:
For starters honestly this game doesnt deserve the amount of hate it is getting. Yes its a mobile game but its fun. its rockpaperscissors with abbilties and rpg elements. 

A lot of people have been saying this is entirly luck based. HELLO! have you even played rockpaper scissors? 80% of that game is luck.

That being said even this version of rock paper scissors is not entirly luck based there is stratagy you can use, you can very easily fake out your opponent and trick them in to playing what you want them to (i.e. at the start choose paper twice in a row maybe 3  then switch to rock 80% of the time the ai will swap to scissors) 
the usual stratagy you can use to win rockpaper scissors in real life can also apply here for the most part


overall this game deserves a lot more praise than its getting

7/10

author: {'steamid': '76561198163052647', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 60, 'playtime_forever': 30, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 30, 'last_played': 1469201892}
review:
Es piedra papel o tijeras, con un toque metido a fuerzas de rpg y grindeo, sistema de niveles y mejoras.
Un pay to win en todisima regla e incluso siendo pay to win dependeras muchisimo de la suerte, no de la habilidad....no,
de la suerte, jugue alrededor de 30 minutos y resulta abuuuurrido, jugue un PVP contra un chico con 300 de vida, yo teniendo 120 y le gane, asi que aun si metes tu dinero no garantizara que no seas la m1erda.

No lo recomiendo mas que tal vez para tus hermanos o primitos que no seran quisquillosos y se van a entreneter por la esencia simple del juego, aun asi mejor descargarles un buen  mario o ponerles un juego flash.

PD:Otro juego de celulares en steam.

author: {'steamid': '76561198045381877', 'num_games_owned': 557, 'num_reviews': 2587, 'playtime_forever': 163, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 163, 'last_played': 1468576572}
review: RoShamBo, a Rock, Paper, Scissors game about collecting loot, leveling your character, and recognizing patterns. You can play through the single player city mode, or play against others in the online battle mode. The actual fighting consists of r,p,s along with using your heroes abilities and potions to stay in the fight longer or end it quicker. It looks like there is a large variety of gear to get for your character, but it may require some grinding to get everything you want without paying real money.  Now I for one might think that playing a rock, paper, scissors game is a little silly, but I have to admit the game makes it seem a lot more appealing than it really is. Overall I think its pretty neat.

author: {'steamid': '76561198048974498', 'num_games_owned': 2973, 'num_reviews': 812, 'playtime_forever': 894, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 894, 'last_played': 1474543354}
review:
A short while back, some wacky japesters released a game on Steam called Rock Paper Scissors Champion, and it was...well, shit, perhaps not surprisingly. What a stupid concept for a fully-fledged game, eh? At least it was free-to-play, so not 100% insulting.

   Now a fresh pack of geniuses have decided to release ANOTHER rock-paper-scissors "fight" game, called RoShamBo Arena. And the shocking thing about this one? Er...it's actually not that bad!

   Gameplay-wise, it's hard to argue that there's anything "great" here. It's mostly luck, maybe a little bit of "psychology" in trying to predict your opponent's next move or make your own next move less predictable to them, as well as "strategising" about how and when to make use of your valuable perks. But sure, on the whole, it's mostly down to chance. 

   Aesthetically-speaking, on the other hand, it's quite delightful, with charming graphics and characters, and entertaining music and sound design. Hell, I'd even go so far as to say that it's pretty fun, at least for a while. Hell, it's maybe even the teeniest, tiniest bit addictive. But only slightly.

   Is it the "second coming" of...anything? Well, it's the second "free-to-play" rock-paper-scissors game to try its luck on Steam in the past six months, but apart from that...no, it's not. It's just a trifling piece of entertainment, which you can apparently waste oodles of real-world money on to get the upper hand on the other guy, which I really can't see why anyone would bother doing since I can't see why anyone would bother spending oodles of TIME on it, period. 

   But it's definitely worth a download and just a teensy-weensy bit of your time, especially if you occasionally crave something a bit semi-mindless and, well, kinda "easy", at least on the old brain (though I have managed to beat more than half of my opponents so far, be it by sheer luck or otherwise).

   By far the best rock-paper-scissors game I've played on Steam this year. I'll leave it up to the individual to decide how significant a statement that is.

Verdict: 7.5/10.

UPDATE: Okay, so it's only a handful of days later, and I've now clocked up over seven hours on this game, so perhaps a slight update is in order? So yeah, fair enough...it's not "slightly" addictive, it's perhaps a tad more than that. And while I still don't see myself or anyone else getting up, say, HUNDREDS of hours on the fucking thing (please, God, NO), I can safely say that it's quite compelling in its own odd way. If you're not above a bit of light-hearted "fun", definitely give it a go. Oh, and I suppose I should raise that Verdict slightly in accordance...

Updated Verdict: 8/10.
